summary: DURING SPORADIC TIMES, THE INSIDE OF THE CAR WILL START SMELLING LIKE ROTTEN EGGS.  THERE IS NO CORRELATION TO HOW LONG WE HAVE BEEN IN THE CAR OR A CERTAIN SPEED.  THE SMELL WILL COME AND GO.  SOMETIMES THE SMELL IS NOTICEABLE FROM THE OUTSIDE OF THE CAR ONCE WE HAVE STOPPED AT OUR DESTINATION.  DEALER SAYS THAT THIS IS NORMAL FOR THIS CAR.
